From: Molly Kilete. Abuja The Nigerian Air Force (NAF), has announced the appointment of a new Director of Public Relations  and Information. He is Air Commodore Olatokunbo Adesanya. He takes over from the former spokesman,  Group Captain Ayodele Famuyiwa, who has been redeployed. Until his appointment, Commodore Adesanya was the pioneer Director of Aircraft Quality Assurance at the Headquarters Nigerian Air Force. A member of 37, Course of the Nigerian Defence Academy (NDA) Air Commodore Adesanya,  was commissioned into the Nigerian Air Force as a regular combatant officer on September 22, 1990. He holds a Masters Degree in Development Studies and a Bachelor of Science Degree in Chemistry from the NDA, Kaduna.  He also has a Post Graduate Certificate in Aeromechanical Engineering from the Air Force Institute of Technology (AFIT), Kaduna, a Diploma in Computer Engineering and a Certificate of Proficiency in Information Systems Management.